      <title>21. How to do good and do good business, w/Starbucks' Howard Schultz</title>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>You can make your social impact and your bottom line work hand-in-hand. But you'll have to be as creative and innovative about your company's values as you are about the business itself. Howard Schultz, chair and former CEO of Starbucks, not only changed how America wakes up, but set new standards for employee benefits. From offering college tuition to American employees to providing health care for employees' parents in China, Howard has always been one step ahead of the social impact curve.</p><p>Read a transcript of this interview at:&nbsp;<a href="https://mastersofscale.com/howard-schultz-how-to-do-good-and-do-good-business/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://mastersofscale.com/howard-schultz-how-to-do-good-and-do-good-business/</a></p><p>Subscribe to the Masters of Scale weekly newsletter:&nbsp;<a href="https://mastersofscale.com/subscribe" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://mastersofscale.com/subscribe</a></p><p>See Privacy Policy at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy</a> and California Privacy Notice at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info</a>.</p>]]>
