      <title>9. The next Silicon Valley is...? w/Endeavor's Linda Rottenberg</title>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>What’s the secret to Silicon Valley's thriving startup scene? And can that kind of ecosystem happen anywhere else in the world? Linda Rottenberg, CEO of Endeavor, makes the case that a startup culture can be nurtured almost anywhere, so long as you have the raw ingredients — starting with a few initial entrepreneurs with access to capital and a willingness to pay it forward. From Buenos Aires to Boston, Tel Aviv to Shenzen, hear Linda's stories of global startup scenes that could give Silicon Valley a run for its money.</p><p>Read a transcript of this interview at:&nbsp;<a href="https://mastersofscale.com/linda-rottenberg-the-next-silicon-valley/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://mastersofscale.com/linda-rottenberg-the-next-silicon-valley/</a></p><p>Subscribe to the Masters of Scale weekly newsletter:&nbsp;<a href="https://mastersofscale.com/subscribe" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://mastersofscale.com/subscribe</a></p><p>See Privacy Policy at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy</a> and California Privacy Notice at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info</a>.</p>]]>
